# MOBILE-FIRST BEST PRACTICES

## BREAKPOINTS
- **768px**: PRIMARY (tablet/mobile boundary)
- **1024px**: Desktop
- **1280px**: Large desktop

## MOBILE-FIRST CSS
```css
/* Mobile base */ .nav { display: none; }
/* Desktop enhance */ @media (min-width: 768px) { .nav { display: flex; } }
```

## TOUCH TARGETS (WCAG 2.1 AAA)
- **44x44px** minimum, **48x48px** recommended, spacing ≥8px

## VIEWPORT
```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=5.0, user-scalable=yes">
```

## VAADIN
```java
// AppLayout: auto-overlay <768px
layout.addToDrawer(mobileMenu); layout.addToNavbar(desktopMenu);
// FormLayout: responsive
form.setResponsiveSteps(new ResponsiveStep("0", 1), new ResponsiveStep("768px", 2));
```

## VAADIN BUTTON MOBILE OPTIMIZATION
```css
@media (max-width: 767px) {
    .button-class::part(label) { display: none; } /* Hide text via Shadow DOM */
    .button-class { width: 44px; height: 44px; padding: 0; }
    .button-class vaadin-icon { position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); }
}
```

## CRITICAL ANTIPATTERNS
1. Fixed widths → max-width: 100%
2. user-scalable=no → accessibility violation
3. Touch targets <44px → WCAG fail
4. Desktop-first @media (max-width) → use min-width
5. Font-size <16px → iOS zooms
